[{"id":"VR625274","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A satellite is in a circular orbit around Earth. In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, the radius of the satellite’s orbit is changed slightly such that the gravitational potential energy of the satellite-Earth system increases. In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, the radius of the satellite’s orbit is changed slightly such that the gravitational potential energy of the satellite-Earth system decreases. Which of the following correctly indicates how the radius of the satellite’s orbit changes in each scenario?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1\"/><col class=\"colspec colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:110\"/><col class=\"colspec colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:110\"/><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span></th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span></th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody valign:middle\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Radius increases</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Radius increases</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Radius increases</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Radius decreases</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td cla